00:42:40.869 --> 00:42:50.349
&gt;&gt;male#4: So, you talked a lot about adaptability
and a lot about dynamic systems, but it's

00:42:50.349 --> 00:42:55.480
not really clear what exactly the definition
of adaptability is.

00:42:55.480 --> 00:43:01.430
I mean, we have a naive understanding of it,
but I can't really think of a formal definition

00:43:01.430 --> 00:43:03.079
that fits in with everything.

00:43:03.079 --> 00:43:06.700
&gt;&gt;Rafe Sagarin: Yeah, you can make a formal
definition for adaptability.

00:43:06.700 --> 00:43:07.700
There's been a bunch.

00:43:07.700 --> 00:43:13.260
It's changing in response to changes in the
environment or something like that.

00:43:13.260 --> 00:43:21.200
But I much prefer to define it by showing
how it's been done in many different cases

00:43:21.200 --> 00:43:29.270
over billions of years, because part of getting
value out of the concept of adaptability is

00:43:29.270 --> 00:43:36.990
to see all the diverse ways in which adaptable
systems have used it.

00:43:36.990 --> 00:43:43.079
A ground squirrel does it completely differently
than an octopus, but they both run around

00:43:43.079 --> 00:43:48.839
these same basic themes of decentralized approaches
and how to use information and how to use

00:43:48.839 --> 00:43:51.460
symbiosis.

00:43:51.460 --> 00:43:56.680
It's a simple concept, just changing in response
to a changing environment, but it's that diversity

00:43:56.680 --> 00:44:01.829
underneath the concept, and the fact that
that diversity coalesces around a few key

00:44:01.829 --> 00:44:08.819
themes that makes it such a powerful concept
for use.

00:44:08.819 --> 00:44:16.190
