00:44:31.400 --> 00:44:32.400
We think about the Department of Defense,
or RIAM, or Google as fairly large organizations

00:44:32.400 --> 00:44:34.470
who take a long time to adapt.

00:44:34.470 --> 00:44:40.690
Species generally take a long time to adapt.

00:44:40.690 --> 00:44:48.059
You could argue the octopus changes in a few
minutes underwater.

00:44:48.059 --> 00:44:49.412
As you mentioned, there's different ways of
defining adaptability, but it seems like it

00:44:49.412 --> 00:44:50.412
can often take centuries.

00:44:50.412 --> 00:44:51.412
I guess I'm curious to hear how organizations
often just don't have that kind of time on

00:44:51.412 --> 00:44:52.412
their hands.

00:44:52.412 --> 00:44:53.520
&gt;&gt;Rafe Sagarin: I'm glad you raise the issue
of the timing of adaptation, because there's

00:44:53.520 --> 00:44:55.470
a lot of misconceptions out there.

00:44:55.470 --> 00:45:01.289
We often think of adaptation as this huge
multigenerational thing that will only be

00:45:01.289 --> 00:45:05.890
apparent once you look back in millions of
years at the fossil record.

00:45:05.890 --> 00:45:12.230
But in fact, like most biological systems,
and I talk about this in the book a lot, biological

00:45:12.230 --> 00:45:14.960
systems are nested in every way.

00:45:14.960 --> 00:45:20.650
The same kind of things you see at the genetic
level occur at the cellular level, at the

00:45:20.650 --> 00:45:23.460
organismal level, at the ecosystem level.

00:45:23.460 --> 00:45:27.519
They're nested, and it's likewise nested in
time.

00:45:27.519 --> 00:45:30.869
Adaptability occurs on all these different
nested time scales.

00:45:30.869 --> 00:45:33.400
It occurs virtually instantly.

00:45:33.400 --> 00:45:36.210
It occurs fairly quickly like the octopus
changing color.

00:45:36.210 --> 00:45:39.839
And yes, it occurs over multiple multiple
generations.

00:45:39.839 --> 00:45:45.329
But the more we've looked into, as biologists,
adaptable systems, the more we're understanding

00:45:45.329 --> 00:45:47.910
that it's spread across this full spectrum.

00:45:47.910 --> 00:45:53.109
We're just learning, right now literally,
that even our genetic structures are adapting

00:45:53.109 --> 00:46:01.099
in real time and doing some very radical changes
in real time with gene jumping kind of things.

00:46:01.099 --> 00:46:06.190
So there's really no limits on the timing
of adaptation.

